### Refresh Token Authentication Flow Tests
### This demonstrates the complete refresh token authentication flow

### Step 1: Customer Authenticate (Get OTP)
POST https://localhost:5001/auth/customer-authenticate
Accept: application/json
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "vlad.crishan20@gmail.com"
}

###

### Step 2: Verify OTP (Get Access + Refresh Tokens)
POST https://localhost:5001/auth/verify-otp
Accept: application/json
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "vlad.crishan20@gmail.com",
  "code": "123456"
}

# Response will include:
# - accessToken (short-lived, 30 minutes)
# - refreshToken (long-lived, 30 days)
# - accessTokenExpiresAt
# - refreshTokenExpiresAt

###

### Step 3: Use Access Token for API Calls
GET https://localhost:5001/customer/info
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE
Accept: application/json
Content-Type: application/json

###

### Step 4: Refresh Access Token (when it expires)
POST https://localhost:5001/auth/refresh-token
Accept: application/json
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "token": "YOUR_REFRESH_TOKEN_HERE"
}

# Response will include:
# - New accessToken
# - New refreshToken (old one is revoked)
# - New expiration times

###

### Step 5: Validate Access Token
POST https://localhost:5001/auth/validate-auth-token
Accept: application/json
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "accessToken": "Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE"
}

# Response will include:
# - isValid: true/false
# - customerId
# - email
# - expiresAt

###

### Step 6: Logout (Revoke Refresh Token)
POST https://localhost:5001/auth/customer/logout
Accept: application/json
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "YOUR_REFRESH_TOKEN_HERE"
}

###

### Example: Complete Flow with Real Tokens
### After getting tokens from Step 2, use them here:

### Test with Access Token
GET https://localhost:5001/customer/info
Authorization: Bearer eyJ0eXAiOiJKV1QiLCJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiI...
Accept: application/json

###

### Refresh when Access Token expires
POST https://localhost:5001/auth/refresh-token
Accept: application/json
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "token": "base64-encoded-refresh-token-here"
}

###

### Validate Token
POST https://localhost:5001/auth/validate-auth-token
Accept: application/json
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "accessToken": "Bearer eyJ0eXAiOiJKV1QiLCJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiI..."
}

###

### Logout and Revoke
POST https://localhost:5001/auth/customer/logout
Accept: application/json
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "base64-encoded-refresh-token-here"
}

###

### Security Features Demonstrated:
# 1. Short-lived access tokens (30 minutes)
# 2. Long-lived refresh tokens (30 days) 
# 3. Automatic token rotation on refresh
# 4. Token revocation on logout
# 5. Device and IP tracking
# 6. Token validation endpoint
